==English==

===Verb===
'''to [[pass]] [[for]]'''

#{{transitive}} To be mistakenly seen as something that one is not
#*: '''2006''' [http://www.newyorker.com/fact/content/articles/060731fa_fact The New Yorker] ''When I visited the offices in March, the walls were bare, the furniture battered. With the addition of a dead plant, the suite could '''pass for''' a graduate-student lounge.''